Well, in the last day or so, I've been working on ths map, surf_lineatric. It's not meant to be particularly hard, but some bits will frustrate you, quite a lot. I have built the cubemaps, but it doesn't appear so. I have removed fall damage, and have included both lighting and fog. All textures are default. The only bugs so far are on the 2nd ramp, going to slow will cause you to stop, and on the 2nd last ramp, there is a small mesh failure, but it will not stopyou. I am currently fixing these now.

Constructive Criticism would be greatly appreciated.

-=surf_lessons made by [WF] Helix=-

This map was ment to be released for my clanmembers only, but I decided to release it publically instead so other people can learn how to surf in a playful way aswell.
This is my first map ever.

-The basics-

The map is designed to teach you who to surf. You can find questionmarks on every surf stage. When you stand inside of this, full instructions will be given to you, telling you how to complete a stage.
There are 7 stages, advancing in difficulty. When you complete the map, you will be teleported back to the spawn where you can pick a bonus stage to practice surfing on a higher difficulty level.
Please note that the map has no jail or anything. This will give you unlimited surfing time.

-Bonus stages-

The bonus stages need to be activated before you can play them. You can do this by pressing secret buttons that are hidden somewhere in the 7 lessonstages. There is a total of 3. They are hidden and invisible. Once pressed, the teleporter at the spawn to the dedicated bonus stage will be activated. When pressing such button, you will be notified which stage is unlocked.
Can you find them?


I hope you will have fun, and of course that you will learn something from this.
If you have any questions or comments, feel free to message me over Xfire by adding me as a friend under the name ''gforce2314''

Cheers.

Lots of minor bug fixes to surf_legends, and the jail of the map is lit up.  I'm not too happy with the way the lighting in the jail came out, but it does look nicer than it did.
I fixed up my old map surf_temple and added a LOT to it like another whole course and an awesome jail.  Everyone who helped test this map really enjoyed it, so I hope you have fun with it.

You might notice that this map borrows heavily from the roof area of dune, I found that alot of the time people spent was up there, so I revamped the roof and put it in its own map with ways to speed up (conveyors) except for the very top of the map, there are always two multicolored paths, the one on the right side will always push you forward (jump for more speed.)

No weapons placed on the map (buy zones in spawns.), bombs can be planted on the middle five glass bridges between the two halves of the roof. Bombs can be found within the middle cavity of the map on top of the ramp where there are notches cut into it.

Falling off the map will teleport you into the pseudo-jail. The part you're teleported to is intentionally dark, but you can find your way out easily then use the conveyors to fly out of the middle area and back to where the bombs can be planted/defused.

This is just a slight modification of surf_leet_xl_beta7z.  It was pretty much just a joke at the beginning, but it came out looking kind of nice so I'm releasing it.  I don't know who the author of surf_leet_xl_beta7z is otherwise I'd give credit, but props to whoever did make the original.  It's still fun even after months of surfing.

Also visit my site http://forums.solidsurf.info if you enjoy surf mapping for CS:S

Surf_leet_xl_knifefights
--------------------------

There once was a time when no one knew what the inside of spawn was used for, but we now know it's used to knifefight!

I took cpatton's version of knifefights and fixed a few bugs with the map, I also added a kill button for the knife area (to hinder camping), m3 and deagle spawners (because you can't keep weps every round), and I lit the map. In addition to being lit, a shitload of optimization work was done to increase fps and lower file size.

Thanks goes to SolidSurf Studios, Cpatton, and Jason from NY Fiber.

The map is decompile protected. If you'd like to use it, or have any questions, please pm me.

Enjoy!
